address: {'street': 'Hong Kong, Kowloon, Hong Kong', 'suburb': 'Mong Kok', 'government_area': 'Yau Tsim Mong', 'market': 'Hong Kong', 'country': 'Hong Kong', 'country_code': 'HK', 'location': {'type': 'Point', 'coordinates': [114.16203, 22.32547], 'is_location_exact': True}}
reviews: [{'_id': '418396322', 'date': datetime.datetime(2019, 3, 2, 5, 0), 'listing_id': '23026295', 'reviewer_id': '139987508', 'reviewer_name': 'Rong', 'comments': '房东人很好,虽然没有见到但是 (Hidden by Airbnb) 上响应很快,基本随时响应,态度也很好,会为你解决问题,熟了也会开玩笑｡入住是自助的密码入住,很方便快捷｡\n房源的话我觉得在香港绝对是性价比超高的了,房间和图片上一模一样,没有差别,非常干净整洁,大小也比同等价位的要宽敞很多｡床上用品超级柔软舒服(感动!),有电视,有微波炉(我热了一次鸡蛋仔)和电冰箱(我们用来保存ladyM的蛋糕),使得我们在房间里吃东西很方便｡当然也有美中不足,一是房源位置不太好找,距离太子地铁站要走上十几分钟,还是有点小偏,建议跟着导航走,晚上回宿舍的路上穿过小公园的时候会看到南亚人,作为女生有点害怕…建议还是结伴而行;二是没有soap和晾衣架,建议房东之后提供~三是热水器一定要开一会再洗澡!要不然就是冷水澡了｡整体来说还是很值的'}]

name: Main Retreat
amenities: ['TV', 'Wifi', 'Pool', 'Kitchen', 'Free parking on premises', 'Pets allowed', 'Free street parking', 'Family/kid friendly', 'Suitable for events', 'Washer', 'Dryer', 'Smoke detector', 'Carbon monoxide detector', 'First aid kit', 'Fire extinguisher', 'Essentials', 'Shampoo', 'Lock on bedroom door', 'Hangers', 'Hair dryer', 'Iron', 'Laptop friendly workspace', 'Self check-in', 'Building staff', 'Private entrance', 'High chair', 'Children’s books and toys', 'Crib', 'Pack ’n Play/travel crib', 'Hot water', 'Luggage dropoff allowed', 'Long term stays allowed']
reviews: [{'_id': '410182374', 'date': datetime.datetime(2019, 2, 9, 5, 0), 'listing_id': '28438885', 'reviewer_id': '127737356', 'reviewer_name': 'Liz', 'comments': "Troy's place is absolutely AMAZING! I so wish we had had more downtime here, because the spot is SO COOL. The Main Retreat was very clean, had a nice bathroom, kitchen, and amenities. It was also very nicely decorated. But none of this compares to the view: It.Is. STUNNING. You get a great view of the ocean as well as a lot of the beautiful jungle vegetation-the pictures don't do it justice! There are a couple of other rental properties onsite, but because this is a top-floor unit, it still seems very private. This is in the jungle, so it is inevitable that a couple of critters will make their way in (small geckos and bugs), but we just kept the windows closed after we got there and did not have any issues. The condo is about 15 minutes from the town of Paia and less than 10 from Mamas Fish House and Ho'okipa beach. What was also great is that this place is right at the beginning of the Road to Hana. The guy onsite (I didn't catch his name) was extremely friendly and helpful, and helped us borrow some snorkel gear and beach chairs. All in all, I would definitely recommend this place for any adventure loving couple or small family who wants a gorgeous view!"}, {'_id': '415097833', 'date': datetime.datetime(2019, 2, 21, 5, 0), 'listing_id': '28438885', 'reviewer_id': '7709117', 'reviewer_name': 'Dan', 'comments': 'Such a beautiful spot and super friendly, helpful hosts. Even helped us arrange a fantastic babysitter. Hope to be back soon!'}]

[{'_id': '415476373', 'date': datetime.datetime(2019, 2, 22, 5, 0), 'listing_id': '31040144', 'reviewer_id': '51023377', 'reviewer_name': 'John', 'comments': 'The best AirBnB experience we've had (out of 9). It's a beautiful,  safe, and private locale with top amenities.

- Safe: the facilities are only accessible with an encoded plastic "key". This gets you inside the buildings, use of the elevator, into your room, onto the grounds. You even have to use it to get OUT of the private grounds and onto the lagoon (a feature, not a bug).
- Private: it's away from the hustle N bustle of Honolulu, but that's just a 45 min drive away on the H1. The grounds are manicured daily,  lots of trees and Hawaiian flora. The Koi ponds are a big hit with the keiki (children). 
- Amenities: Our lanai had 4 beach chairs, 2 bogey boards, a mid-sized ice cooler, and children's beach toys. You can open up the 'wall' to the lanai and make it feel like its part of the room. The kitchen was fully loaded with what we needed to cook, including a cork screw. I liked that the master suite had its own thermostat for the air conditioner. Nice master bathroom too. The WIFI worked. If I had questions regarding the unit, I got answers within hours, not days. There are restaurants and stores about a 7 min walk away, including Roy's, an upper-scale place to get good island cuisine.'}]

name: Spacious room with private floor in 3 story home
amenities: ['TV', 'Wifi', 'Kitchen', 'Free street parking', 'Heating', 'Washer', 'Dryer', 'Smoke detector', 'First aid kit', 'Essentials', 'Lock on bedroom door', 'Hangers', 'Iron', 'Laptop friendly workspace', 'Hot water', 'Microwave', 'Coffee maker', 'Refrigerator', 'Dishwasher', 'Dishes and silverware', 'Cooking basics', 'Oven', 'Stove', 'BBQ grill', 'Garden or backyard', 'Long term stays allowed', 'Other']
reviews:
[{'_id': '414185104', 'date': datetime.datetime(2019, 2, 18, 5, 0), 'listing_id': '31318633', 'reviewer_id': '27649517', 'reviewer_name': 'Field', 'comments': "Naturally the first thing that is most unique about staying at Andy’s place is that you are living in an attic/loft with 2 skylight windows that bring in plenty of sunshine! It’s not everyday you get to wake up with the sun shining down on you which made waking up very pleasant just busking in the morning light. 

Second of all, I don’t think we’ve ever been on a more comfortable bed. Every night we fall asleep so easily and soundly and every morning it takes us ages to get off the bed because it’s really just that comfortable. You have to try it to believe it.

While Andy wasn’t around in the place, her friend Jacque was and she was the warmest person ever. We were late checking in on the first night and she waited for us to get back so she could welcome us in. 

The toilets are also very extremely clean and well fitted, hot water readily available.

Andy also lives in a really nice quiet neighbourhood that isn't too far off from the city too, which is great cos travelling is convenient and you still get to come home to peace and quiet. That being said, there are plenty of great cafe's and eateries around the neighbourhood, so if you feel like avoiding the city hustle, you're covered.

All in all, we can’t recommend Andy’s place enough and we will definitely be back again soon!"}, {'_id': '417076579', 'date': datetime.datetime(2019, 2, 26, 5, 0), 'listing_id': '31318633', 'reviewer_id': '90140539', 'reviewer_name': 'Hyeseul', 'comments': 'Andy’s place was a lovely, bright and sunny room even though it was a bit far from lightrail or bus stops. I stayed for one week and it was a perfect choice for me. It have spacious bed and all the lovely objets, and the view of the city was beautiful.'}, {'_id': '419825790', 'date': datetime.datetime(2019, 3, 4, 5, 0), 'listing_id': '31318633', 'reviewer_id': '16609191', 'reviewer_name': 'Anne Marie', 'comments': "Andy's place is really lovely, check-in was simple and is a good proximity to Sydney CBD an as well as some lovely bay walks. Housemates are super welcoming and the kitchen is equipped with basic necessities to cook in the kitchen. The room is a little bit warm in the summer due to being on the top floor but Andy has provided a fan. The room was very clean and spacious with comfy pillows and nice bedding. Highly recommend!"}]
